==English==

===Etymology===
From Italian ''[[fermare]]'', stop.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/fɜːˈmɑːtə/}} (''[[RP]]'')
*{{IPA|/fɜːrˈmɑːtə/}} (''US'')

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

[[Image:Fermata.png|thumb|Diagram of a note shown with a fermata.]]
# ''(Music):'' A [[notation]] to hold a [[note]] for longer than its usual duration, until the conductor cuts it off.  Usually represented as a dot with a semi-circle above it, written above the [[clef]].
 
